President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Robert Porter Jackson has been nominated as the Ambassador to the Republic of Ghana at the Department of State. He is a career member of the Foreign Service and currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary for African Affairs. Michael Michaud has been nominated as the Assistant Secretary for Veterans' Employment and Training at the Department of Labor. He previously served as the United States Representative for the Second Congressional District of Maine and was chosen as the Ranking Member of the House Committee on Veterans' Affairs. John E. Sparks has been nominated as a Judge for the United States Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces. He is currently the Commissioner to the Chief Judge of the Court and has held various positions in the military and legal field.